OB:
When I try to create a FontRegistry instance for my application using the following code:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
    FontRegistry fonts = new FontRegistry("com.company.product.fonts");
}

I get a MissingResourceException. However, if I try this instead:

com.company.product.MyClass

public void createFontRegistry(){
    ResourceBundle fonts = ResourceBundle.getBundle("com.company.product.fonts");
}

There is no exception. Moreover, if I create a complete copy of the FontRegistry class in my com.company.product package, then it works. My guess is it is a bug in the FontRegistry. It tries to load the fonts resource bundle, but the FontRegistry's class loader is used to do that (see readResourceBundle(String) FontRegistry method).
